The campaign train of the wife of former vice president and presidential candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), Rukayya Atiku Abubakar, has arrived Jigawa state. Atiku’s wife, while in Dutse, paid a homage to the Emir of Dutse, Alhaji Muhammad Nuhu Sanusi. Mrs. Abubakar, who is also a princess from the royal family of Adamawa emirate, solicited for the support and blessing of the royal father for the presidential ambition of her husband. In his remark, the Emir of Dutse urged politicians to play politics in accordance to its dictates saying, this is fundamental for ensuring a peaceful conduct of the forthcoming general election. Atiku’s wife pledges effective women empowerment 2019: I won't step down for Atiku -  Lamido Atiku asks ex gov Sule Lamido to step aside for him